DATA CLOUD
Create a B2C Commerce Activation for a Segment

After you set required data field mappings and then create a segment in Data Cloud, create a B2C Commerce activation to publish the segment.

In Data Cloud, click Segments and select a segment.
From Activations, click New.
Select a B2C Commerce activation target.
In Activation Membership, the data model object (DMO) is chosen by default.
Click Continue.
To filter the activation data, select one or more data sources.
If you select a B2C Commerce data source, all activated attributes must have valid values since they can’t be left blank or null. If you select a non-B2C Commerce data source (for example: Amazon S3), make sure CustomerNo and CustomerListId activated attributes have valid values.
Valid values are populated only when the field mappings are done correctly for all data sources.
Enter a name and description for your activation.
IMPORTANT You can’t include the following characters in the name field: + ! @ # $ % ^ * ( ) = { } [ ] \ . < > / " : ? | , _ &
Click Save.

Your segment publishes on the next publish scheduled for the selected activation target.
